article.headline: DAVIDSON 82, SMS 71
article.story:
SPRINGFIELD, Missouri (Ticker) -- Brendan Winters scored 22 
points and sparked a big second half as Davidson posted an 82-71
victory over Southwest Missouri State in an NIT first-round
matchup.

Winters scored 16 of his points after the break to help the
Wildcats overcome a 32-28 halftime deficit.

Davidson (23-8) made 15-of-29 3-pointers, including 9-of-14 in
the second half.  Winters made all four of his 3-pointers in the
final 20 minutes and was 7-of-10 from the floor, including
6-of-8 from the arc, overall.

Southwest Missouri State (19-13) shot only 35 percent (12-of-34)
in the second half and was buried by the barrage of Davidson
3-pointers.

Jason Morton scored 19 points and fellow reserve Ian Johnson
added 14 for Davidson.

Deke Thompson had 15 points and Anthony Shavies 14 for the
Bears.
